      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:3:34:2",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) مَنْ لَمْ يَعْرِفْ شَيْئاً هَلْ عَلَيْهِ شَيْ‏ءٌ قَالَ لَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Al Hajjal, from Sa’alba Bin Maymoun, from Abdul A’ala Bin Ayn who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, ‘The one who does not recognise anything, is there anything upon him?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘No’."
        ]
      }
